-- Alvarion Rises After Mobile Carrier Uses Wi-Fi Services in China
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-04-24T08:22:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/alvarion-rises-after-mobile-carrier-uses-wi-fi-services-in-china.html
Alvarion Ltd. (ALVR)  rose to the highest
level in almost three weeks after the telecommunications
equipment maker said a mobile carrier has deployed its Wi-Fi
base stations for high-speed internet access in  China .  The  stock  rallied 13.3 percent to 3.22 shekels, the highest
intraday level since April 5, at 11:11 a.m. in Tel Aviv.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
